{
  "name": "Warding Maneuver",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/skills/melee/shield-block-bash-blue.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 7th level, you learn to fend off strikes directed at you, your mount, or other creatures nearby. If you or a creature you can see within <strong>5 feet</strong> of you is hit by an attack, you can roll [[/r 1d8]] as a <strong>reaction </strong>if you're wielding a melee weapon or a shield. Roll the die, and add the number rolled to the target's AC against that attack. If the attack still hits, the target has resistance against the attack's damage.</p>\n<p>You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Constitution modifier (a minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses of it when you finish a long rest.</p>",
